<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-10224] The license term about jersey is not correct</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-10224</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Kafka 2.3.0 and later bundle jersey 2.28. Since 2.28, jersey changed the license type from&#160;CDDL/GPLv2+CPE to EPLv2. But in Kafka 2.5.0&apos;s LICENSE file&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/2.5/LICENSE&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/2.5/LICENSE&lt;/a&gt;, it still said&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;This distribution has a binary dependency on jersey, which is available under the CDDL&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be corrected ASAP.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
